   <text>
      <body>
         <head>To <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0355.xml"/>Clayton Carthy</persName><note
               place="foot" n="1"><persName><ref target="/persons/pers0355.xml"/>Clayton
                  Carthy</persName> does not appear in any list of <seg ana="itinerancy"
                  >itinerants</seg>. He was apparently serving as <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s book steward in
                  <placeName>Bristol</placeName>, assisting with compiling the fourth volume of <hi
                  rend="italic">Sermons on Several Occasions</hi>, which <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> finished in early <date
                  when="1759-10">Oct. 1759</date> (see <hi rend="italic">Journal</hi>, 21:231 in
               this edn.).</note></head>
         <opener><placeName>Newcastle-Upon-Tyne</placeName><lb/><date when="1759-06-12">June 12,
               1759</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute>Dear Clayton,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>I hope you have received the sermon upon the New Birth.<note place="foot" n="2">Sermon
               45, &apos;The New Birth&apos; (2:187â€“201 in this edn.).</note> I can easily send you
            one a week. I have finished eight, and am now transcribing the fourth. You should supply
            any word that is wanting.</p>
         <p>Go east, west, north, or south, to <placeName>Norton</placeName><note place="foot" n="3"
                  ><placeName>Norton St Philip</placeName> between <placeName>Bath</placeName> and
                  <placeName>Frome</placeName>.</note> or elsewhere, and speak sense or nonsense for
            a quarter of an hour. I believe it will avail both for your soul and body more than you
            imagine.</p>
         <p>I do &apos;think what is doing&apos;.<note place="foot" n="4"><persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers0355.xml"/>Carthy</persName> had apparently asked if
                     <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> was aware of the
               turmoil being caused by his estrangement with his wife <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers2091.xml"/>Mary</persName>.</note> By this post (to leave
            that poor sinner without excuse) I have wrote once more in the following words:</p>
         <p>
            <quote>
               <l>I make you one more offer. Only leave off speaking against me behind my back
                  (whereby you do not hurt me, but the cause of God) and restore my papers to me,
                  and you will find me,</l>
               <l>Your still affectionate husband,</l>
            </quote>
         </p>
         <closer>My part is to go on my way and to finish my work. I am, dear Clayton,<lb/>
            <signed>Yours affectionately,<lb/><persName>J. Wesley</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
   </text>
